<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1542,1963]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,510,1722,1747]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[523,755,1722,1747]" class="Reptilia" family="Hoplocercidae" genus="Enyalioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis box="[523,755,1722,1747]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Enyalioides laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to western Amazonia, reaching eastward the Roosevelt River on the south of Amazon River, and the lower Japurá River on the north of Amazon River, occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[300,371,1794,1819]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[385,498,1794,1819]" name="Colombia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[513,608,1794,1819]" name="Ecuador" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[672,723,1795,1818]" name="Peru" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[742,813,1794,1819]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1124,1146]" captionTargetBox="[154,1428,203,1093]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1102]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Distribution of examined material of Enyalioides laticeps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234989/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[797,813,1795,1819]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[871,942,1794,1819]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is known from the states of Amazonas, Acre, and Rondônia. 
<taxonomicName box="[396,625,1830,1855]" class="Reptilia" family="Hoplocercidae" genus="Enyalioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis box="[396,625,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Enyalioides laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is arboreal and diurnal, inhabits primary and (occasionally) secondary forests and varzea, where it is found mainly on trunks of small trees or palms at 
<number box="[1050,1092,1867,1891]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
meters above ground, but also on branches and palm fronds, on rooting stumps, and on the ground (
<bibRefCitation author="Duellman" box="[934,1113,1902,1927]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Duellman, W. E. (1973) Descriptions of new lizards from the upper Amazon basin. Herpetologica, 29, 228 - 231." type="journal article" year="1973">
Duellman 
<number box="[1054,1113,1903,1927]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duellman" box="[1126,1185,1903,1927]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Duellman, W. E. (1978) The biology of an equatorial herpetofauna in Amazonian Ecuador. Miscellaneous Publications, Museum of Natural History of University of Kansas, 65, 1 - 352." type="journal article" year="1978">
